President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the state of Texas, authorizing federal aid to support recovery efforts following wildfires that began on August 30, 2011. The declaration makes federal funding available to affected individuals in Bastrop County, including grants for temporary housing, home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other assistance programs. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) is coordinating federal recovery operations in the affected area, with additional assessments ongoing in other areas. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by phone. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.